    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "-1 - many people will be using it with only Python 3 installed, and we want the command `ipython` to work for them.\r\n\r\nThis is also consistent with how conda environments and virtualenvs work: they contain only one version of Python, which can be used as `python` inside the environment."
