    "updated_at": "2017-12-12T19:54:40Z",
    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "* Not everybody is following that recommendation, so it's already not terribly useful.\r\n* Almost every Python package that installs scripts does this - pip, pytest, pep8, and so on. If you install it on both versions of Python, the last one installed 'wins' the script.\r\n* Downstream packagers like Linux distros can and do handle this differently in line with their own policies."
